                    <h3 class="mod" data-uuid="f67a6181a7f74752ba2d0115f8044243">The South, 1790–1860</h3>
                    <p class="mod" data-uuid="451c9b66f0a84986a5cce6728d9824ef">The cotton gin dramatically increased cotton
                        production in the South, creating a demand for more slaves. An early U.S.
                        antislavery measure was a ban on importing slaves, but it did not ban slavery itself. By this time, France had already outlawed slavery in its colonies and Britain had banned slave trading
                        throughout its empire. Slave revolts caused fear among southerners.<br />
                    </p>
